      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the FDA pump geometry. The coarse-to-medium GCI for the normalized hemolysis index was 7.2% and the medium-to-fine GCI was 6.8%, both exceeding the 5% acceptance threshold. The team concluded that practical constraints on computational resources precluded further refinement; the fine-mesh solution was adopted as best available. Discretization uncertainty is acknowledged but not fully bounded to the required level. The assessment team recorded this as a borderline shortfall and proceeded to acceptance on the basis that experimental comparison provided supplementary confidence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
